thread.title: 1990s nostalgia, Seattle-style

author: LEVI PULKKINEN, SEATTLEPI.COM STAFF
title: 1990s nostalgia, Seattle-style
text:
Eventually, pop nostalgia just happens.
It goes something like this. Youth is a dramatic, consequential time. When the young get older and leave their culture behind, they remember it grandly, recreate their lost youth and pitch it out into the world.
So, world, welcome back to the '90s.
Reports Tuesday are that The Fresh Prince and Jazzy Jeff will be touring this summer , which hopefully means they’ll wind up with Shaq on ABC’s '90s throwback comedy “ Fresh off the Boat .” The “ X-Files ” is back, as is John Stamos . A “ Jurassic ” movie made an obscene amount of money. Nickelodeon is dusting off “Clarissa” and the rest. Even our beloved Columbia Sportswear is calling it a comeback .
All this should be good news for Seattle. We were like the Portland of the '90s.
Check out the gallery above for some of the most nostalgia-worthy people and happenings from Seattle’s hippest years.
If you’ve got additions, tweet @levipulk and tell me what I’m missing. You can follow me, too, though it's mostly crime news.
